==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punter
<hw>Punt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ponte</ets>. See <er>Punt</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>One
who punts; specifically, one who plays against the banker or dealer, as
in baccara and faro.</def> <rj><au>Hoyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Punter
<hw>Punt"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who punts a football; also, one
who propels a punt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Punter
<hw>Punt"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(London Stock Exchange)</fld>
<def>A scalper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

